 <div\n    class=\"kv-control-placeholder kv-_section\"\n    data-kv-control=\"background\">\n  <\/div> <div class='kv-background  ' style=\" background-color: rgb(237,241,247);\">\n        \n        <div class='kv-background-inner '  style=\"\n          \n          \n          \n          background-color: rgb(237,241,247);\n          \"><\/div>\n          \n<\/div>\n  <div class=\"position-relative kv-content\">\n    <div\n    class=\"kv-control-placeholder kv-_section\"\n    data-kv-control=\"content\">\n  <\/div> <div class=\"kv-ee-section kv-ee-section--lg\"><div class=\"kv-ee-container\"><div class=\"kv-ee-row kv-ee-align-left\"><div class=\"kv-ee-col-md-6 kv-ee-section-text kv-ee-content-text kv-ee-section--md\"> <h2 class=\"kv-ee-section-title kv-ee-section-title--sm\" data-type=\"text\" tabindex=\"0\">Welcome to our website<span data-prop=\"title\" class=\"ck-editable-element\" data-editable=\"basic\" style=\"display:none;\"><\/span><\/h2> <p class=\"kv-ee-section-subtitle kv-ee-subtitle kv-ee-section-subtitle--sm\" data-type=\"text\" tabindex=\"0\">Chinese medicine has been used for treating pain For thousands of years. traditional medicine, especially acupuncture, cupping and moxibustion therapy, has been effective in treating pain and bruises, neck, shoulder, waist and leg pain.<br><br>In Chinese medicine, we called pain &#8220;Bi Syndrome&#8221;\u75f9\u75c7, and divided different pain into &#8220;Cold Bi&#8221;, &#8220;Wet Bi&#8221;, &#8220;Tendon Bi&#8221; and so on.&nbsp;<br><br>Chinese medicine believes that the mechanism of pain generation can be divided into two aspects: pain if there is stagnation inside the body, and pain if it is not nourished. The treatment theory removes the stagnation, activates the meridian and alleviates the pain while nourishing the muscle and tendon if the pain is due to a lack of nourishment. <br>\n\n<br>Generally speaking, from a modern medical point of view, Chinese medicine treatment can promote more blood flow to the pain area, release the inflammation produced during pain and helps with local muscle spasms and injury.&nbsp;<br><br><br><br><br> <span data-prop=\"subtitle\" class=\"ck-editable-element\" data-editable=\"basic\" style=\"display:none;\"><\/span><\/p> <hr class=\"kv-ee-underline\"> <p class=\"kv-ee-section-description kv-ee-mb-4 kv-ee-body--md\" data-type=\"text\" tabindex=\"0\">Chinese medicine can help with the pain of the following symptoms and diseases but is not limited as: <br>\nKnee pain <br>\nNeck pain <br>\nShoulder pain <br>\nLow back pain\n<br>Achilles tendonitis <br>\nAnkle Sprains <br>\nCarpal tunnel syndrome <br>\nRotator cuff injuries <br>\nIlio-tibial band problems <br>\nImpingement Syndrome <br>\nHeadaches and Migraines <br>\nOsteoarthritis \nPain <br>Plantar fasciitis <br>\nRotator cuff injuries <br>\nSciatica <br>\nShin splints <br>\nBursitis of the hip and shoulder\n<br>Tennis and golfers elbow;<span data-prop=\"description\" class=\"ck-editable-element\" data-editable=\"basic\" style=\"display:none;\"><\/span><\/p> <hr class=\"kv-ee-underline\">  <\/div>  <div class=\"kv-ee-col-md-6  \"><div data-aspect-ratio=\"\"class=\"\"> <div\n      data-type=\"image\" data-property=\"image\"\n       class=\"kv-ee-featured-image kv-ee-content-image loader\" role=\"img\" data-src=\"https:\/\/images.builderservices.io\/s\/cdn\/v1.0\/i\/m?url=https%3A%2F%2Fimages.unsplash.com%2Fphoto-1519823551278-64ac92734fb1%3Fcrop%3Dentropy%26cs%3Dtinysrgb%26fit%3Dmax%26fm%3Djpg%26ixid%3DMnw1NTEzfDB8MXxzZWFyY2h8Nnx8YWN1cHVuY3R1cmV8ZW58MHx8fHwxNjYyODMyMzA5%26ixlib%3Drb-1.2.1%26q%3D80%26w%3D100\" data-src-normal=\"https:\/\/images.builderservices.io\/s\/cdn\/v1.0\/i\/m?url=https%3A%2F%2Fimages.unsplash.com%2Fphoto-1519823551278-64ac92734fb1%3Fcrop%3Dentropy%26cs%3Dtinysrgb%26fit%3Dmax%26fm%3Djpg%26ixid%3DMnw1NTEzfDB8MXxzZWFyY2h8Nnx8YWN1cHVuY3R1cmV8ZW58MHx8fHwxNjYyODMyMzA5%26ixlib%3Drb-1.2.1%26q%3D80%26w%3D1000\" data-src-retina=\"https:\/\/images.builderservices.io\/s\/cdn\/v1